    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's clear, thanks. One more thing—if we're using CIF, does the seller have any specific obligation to ensure the insurance policy covers things like cargo damage due to unforeseen maritime accidents or heavy weather? I want to make sure we aren't left hanging if something happens mid-transit.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, absolutely, the seller has a specific obligation under CIF to procure insurance that covers the buyer's risk during transit. This insurance must typically cover risks such as damage from maritime accidents or adverse weather, as required by the CIF term. You should review the insurance policy details provided by the seller to verify the exact coverage level and exclusions before the shipment even leaves Ningbo. This ensures you are protected throughout the journey to Rotterdam.",
      "source": "target",
