      "content": "If a container is lost overboard, your claim would be processed directly through the insurance policy the seller procured under CIF, subject to the policy's terms and conditions. Common disputes often arise from proving causation—distinguishing between risks covered by the policy (like general maritime perils) versus those excluded (like inherent vice or improper packing). Always ensure the insurance policy includes substantive coverage for \"perils of the sea\" and loss at sea to properly protect your interests during transfers.",
